1
00:00:00,540 --> 00:00:02,270
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:03,680
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:07,110
(Episode 13)

4
00:00:17,290 --> 00:00:18,390
(I love you.)

5
00:00:18,460 --> 00:00:19,460
No way.

6
00:00:20,590 --> 00:00:21,590
For real.

7
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:26,100
How did you do all this?

8
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:30,970
For real... What is all this?

9
00:00:32,070 --> 00:00:33,540
(Gong Ju Ah, you are my salvation.)

10
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:44,120
<i>In this world, there is me</i>

11
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:47,650
<i>And with the one who loves me</i>

12
00:00:48,490 --> 00:00:50,660
<i>My Gong Ju Ah</i>

13
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:55,060
<i>I want to walk my own path</i>

14
00:00:55,130 --> 00:00:56,860
<i>Walk my own path</i>

15
00:00:59,830 --> 00:01:01,730
Gong Ju Ah, be my girlfriend.

16
00:01:02,370 --> 00:01:04,600
Let's make today our day one.

17
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:06,140
My gosh.

18
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:08,170
You want me to be your girlfriend?

19
00:01:08,540 --> 00:01:09,970
What, you weren't planning on it?

20
00:01:10,540 --> 00:01:12,510
Not after you came to my place
and kissed me.

21
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:16,610
- And kissed me?
- What?

22
00:01:17,350 --> 00:01:18,380
I did?

23
00:01:20,420 --> 00:01:23,790
You said you missed me.
That you still have feelings for me.

24
00:01:23,990 --> 00:01:25,890
That it was destiny...

25
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,060
I'm going home.

26
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Gong Ju Ah, are you crazy?
Why did you go there?

27
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:09,330
What should I do?

28
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:12,900
I'll take the day off.
Yes, a day off.

29
00:02:13,610 --> 00:02:17,780
No. That's
a really cowardly thing to do.

30
00:02:19,110 --> 00:02:21,980
Right.
I'm responsible for my feelings.

31
00:02:22,210 --> 00:02:24,050
I'm an adult, after all.

32
00:02:27,290 --> 00:02:29,890
But what do I do if he asks me out?

33
00:02:31,090 --> 00:02:32,760
I'm in so much trouble.

34
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,060
What am I going to do? My gosh.

35
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:43,770
Goodness,
why is he sleeping in so late?

36
00:02:44,170 --> 00:02:45,170
Honey.

37
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,940
Gong Jeong Han!

38
00:02:48,540 --> 00:02:49,940
What? What is it?

39
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,610
Did you see it?

40
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,480
What? See what?

41
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:54,910
What?

42
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:57,550
Oh, I must've been dreaming.
Just a weird dream.

43
00:02:58,580 --> 00:03:00,390
But I slept like a baby.

44
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:04,060
Slept like a baby? Please.
You tossed and turned all night.

45
00:03:04,260 --> 00:03:06,590
No, I slept fine. Why?

46
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:10,630
Seong Mi.
How about an early start tomorrow?

47
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:14,370
There's a pour-over coffee place
near the Portobelli restaurant.

48
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,100
It's been a while,
so how about something romantic?

49
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:18,640
Maybe get some morning coffee?

50
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:22,040
You.

51
00:03:22,370 --> 00:03:24,140
What is it?

52
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,380
It's just that
you've been so sweet lately.

53
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:34,550
Really? I've always been this sweet.

54
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:35,990
That's not true.

55
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,590
Anyway, all the nurses are buzzing.

56
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:40,490
They're calling you
a total sweetheart.

57
00:03:42,830 --> 00:03:44,000
What should I wear tomorrow?

58
00:03:44,830 --> 00:03:48,230
You're the most beautiful woman.
You'd look great in anything.

59
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,370
- Go on, wash up.
- Okay.

60
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:04,650
They say you can't live
with a guilty conscience.

61
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,450
I'm dying of anxiety
that I'll get caught.

62
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:08,650
Wait, where can I hide this?

63
00:04:09,390 --> 00:04:12,620
Should I eat it? No, that's right.
I need to keep it as evidence.

64
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,690
What am I going to do with this?

65
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:27,540
You're awake?

66
00:04:27,970 --> 00:04:29,570
What's wrong
with looking a little messy?

67
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:33,080
Over a decade of early mornings
to always look this good.

68
00:04:33,810 --> 00:04:35,250
Of course. I have to.

69
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:37,520
I am a former Miss Gat Kimchi,
you know.

70
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:41,920
Fresh, firm, and green.

71
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:46,460
I'm Cha Se Ri, with zesty charm
just like gat kimchi.

72
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:52,660
My darling,
you were truly beautiful back then.

73
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,500
The harmony of your yin and yang
was perfect, I suppose.

74
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:58,070
The moment I laid eyes on you
back then,

75
00:04:58,470 --> 00:05:00,270
I knew exactly what I felt.

76
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:03,570
"I must have that woman."

77
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:07,150
Honey.

78
00:05:08,610 --> 00:05:12,880
Thank you, honey.
No matter how much time passes,

79
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:15,790
I promise I'll be a woman
who never withers for you.

80
00:05:18,890 --> 00:05:20,830
How about we go on a date tomorrow?
It's been a while.

81
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:23,130
I've got a surprise for you.

82
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:25,800
I'd love that, honey.

83
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,870
But wait a minute.

84
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:31,700
You're not saying this to sway me
into letting the Gong family stay...

85
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:33,240
so you can go on "Human Theater,"
are you?

86
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:34,940
What?

87
00:05:36,370 --> 00:05:37,380
Of course not.

88
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,110
Then hurry up and come on out.

89
00:05:42,850 --> 00:05:46,950
She's incredibly sharp.
Don't back down now, Yang Dong Ik.

90
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:48,250
You've got to push through.

91
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:56,930
Good morning,
President Gong Jeong Han.

92
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,200
Reporting for my morning greetings.

93
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:02,670
I'm at your service
if you need anything.

94
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,400
I'll get everything ready
for our morning exercise.

95
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:06,700
At your service!

96
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:09,410
Is he nuts?
First thing in the morning...

97
00:06:09,670 --> 00:06:10,680
Who was that?

98
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:15,610
What? Oh, a scam message.
Those darn scammers. Goodness.

99
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:18,520
Did they claim to be a prosecutor?
Or did they say someone...

100
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:20,350
opened a fake bank account
in your name?

101
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:24,920
What? Not funny?

102
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:29,560
Ju Ah seems to be in a great mood
this morning.

103
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,500
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.

104
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:34,070
You were out drinking all night
again, weren't you?

105
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:37,170
That I did. Once I start drinking,
it always becomes an all-nighter.

106
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:40,040
Why? Because we live so far away.
But don't worry anymore.

107
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:42,370
Once we move,
I'll be home early every night.

108
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:44,980
That reminds me, Mother,

109
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:49,550
about us going to see
the new house tomorrow...

110
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:51,650
I was wondering
if we could push it back a bit.

111
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,320
Why? Are you busy?

112
00:06:53,650 --> 00:06:58,460
Ju Ah's dad actually asked me out
on a date this morning.

113
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,590
Dad did?

114
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:04,430
Wow. My son is finally growing up,
better late than never.

115
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:06,800
Gosh, you guys are too sweet.

116
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:10,900
It's really wonderful to see
you two so lovey-dovey.

117
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:13,870
Just yesterday,
you discussed divorce,

118
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:15,240
but now you're like newlyweds.

119
00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:17,540
Why do you have to
bring up the past?

120
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:19,640
I'm just so happy these days.

121
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:23,210
By the way,
did Uncle not come home last night?

122
00:07:23,410 --> 00:07:25,620
He didn't come home?
Oh, I just assumed he left early.

123
00:07:25,850 --> 00:07:29,590
He said he had an interview
and was meeting a friend for drinks.

124
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:33,760
He must've been drinking all night.
He's not answering his phone.

125
00:07:34,030 --> 00:07:36,190
He's probably still upset
about what happened with his wife.

126
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:38,760
What can you do?
Time heals all wounds.

127
00:07:38,860 --> 00:07:41,530
No, in cases like this, finding
new love is the best medicine.

128
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:46,270
Their divorce isn't even final yet.
And with your uncle's personality,

129
00:07:46,370 --> 00:07:49,070
I doubt he'll ever be able
to date anyone again.

130
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:56,980
Excuse me, Aunt Se Ri.

131
00:07:57,250 --> 00:08:00,120
Oh, Ji Hu. Tell Grandpa and Uncle
that breakfast is ready.

132
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:02,820
My mom didn't come home last night.

133
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:06,060
- What?
- And she's not answering her phone.

134
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:11,260
Oh! She called me yesterday.

135
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:12,760
She said
she's on a trip with a friend.

136
00:08:13,130 --> 00:08:16,170
Oh, okay.
I was worried for a second.

137
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,070
- I'll go get Grandfather.
- All right.

138
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,840
What does she think she's doing,
not coming home?

139
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,580
- The phone is off. You'll be...
- What?

140
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:28,680
It's off?

141
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:54,510
Hey!

142
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,310
Why did you hit me?

143
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:59,210
What did you do to me?

144
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:00,950
I didn't do anything!

145
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:04,720
Then why did you take
all your clothes off?

146
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,980
My clothes are off because
you threw up on them, Dong Suk.

147
00:09:07,050 --> 00:09:08,750
So I washed them
and hung them up here to dry.

148
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:11,020
Then why were you sleeping
next to me?

149
00:09:11,090 --> 00:09:14,490
Hey, I should be asking you that.
You fell asleep down here.

150
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:15,560
- I did?
- Yes!

151
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:18,900
You threw up, then passed out here.
I tried to go, but you said not to.

152
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:21,530
And you grabbed my ankle.
That's why I ended up sleeping here.

153
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,470
So when did you climb up
onto the bed?

154
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:25,300
Are you sure?
You didn't pull me up here?

155
00:09:25,370 --> 00:09:28,610
This is so unfair! I'm going crazy.
You seriously don't remember?

156
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,410
- I don't.
- Then do you remember...

157
00:09:30,710 --> 00:09:33,980
asking for round two,
to celebrate our breakup?

158
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:35,550
You don't remember
saying that either?

159
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:38,250
- No, I can't remember!
- Hey!

160
00:09:38,580 --> 00:09:40,280
Fine. What's the last thing
you remember?

161
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,490
The last thing I remember?

162
00:09:42,890 --> 00:09:44,260
You're still beautiful.

163
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:46,190
Your eyes are beautiful.

164
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:49,660
Your nose is beautiful,
and your lips are beautiful.

165
00:09:52,830 --> 00:09:54,730
Hey! Why did you hit me again?

166
00:09:54,730 --> 00:09:56,170
- You really have to ask?
- Yes, I have no idea!

167
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:57,470
- Because we kissed.
- No, we didn't.

168
00:09:57,470 --> 00:09:58,700
- We didn't?
- We couldn't.

169
00:09:58,770 --> 00:10:00,910
- Why couldn't we?
- Why do you think?

170
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:09,780
Dong Suk!

171
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:12,120
Goodness...

172
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:16,220
Hey, Dong Suk. Here's a tissue.

173
00:10:17,590 --> 00:10:18,590
My gosh...

174
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:21,260
Hey, wait a second.

175
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:23,160
What? Why?

176
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:31,000
Hey! What the...

177
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:33,300
Oh, right.

178
00:10:33,940 --> 00:10:34,940
"Oh, right?"

179
00:10:35,210 --> 00:10:36,410
I remember that now.

180
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:41,050
The kiss. Yes, the kiss!
You were so drunk,

181
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:44,750
so I said we should call it a night,
but you threw a fit and wouldn't go.

182
00:10:44,820 --> 00:10:47,150
You wanted to go for a second round,
and I said, "No way. I'm not going."

183
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:49,490
And you threw another huge fit.

184
00:10:50,020 --> 00:10:52,460
- Why did you bring me to a motel?
- I brought you?

185
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,520
Then I suppose I brought you?

186
00:10:53,590 --> 00:10:57,500
Actually, yes! You did.
You said we should sleep together.

187
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:00,030
"If they can do it, why can't we?
What's stopping us?"

188
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,470
You said sleeping together
would be revenge!

189
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:02,930
You dragged me here!

190
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:06,170
Well, you can't argue with that.
But you agreed to it.

191
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,440
That's why you came along,
wasn't it?

192
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,510
Hey, Dong Suk... Look.

193
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:14,150
You see, I did not agree to that.

194
00:11:14,210 --> 00:11:16,210
I told you I didn't want to stoop
to the same level as those two.

195
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,780
I made myself perfectly clear.

196
00:11:18,850 --> 00:11:21,520
- Then why did you come with me?
- You want me to show you?

197
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:24,720
Okay, I'll be you.
Dong Suk, this was you last night.

198
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:29,830
"I'm not leaving! Round two!
I'm not leaving!"

199
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:32,600
"I'm not going home! I refuse!"
That's what you were doing! You!

200
00:11:32,660 --> 00:11:35,430
Oh, my goodness.
I can't even deal with myself!

201
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:37,640
You're really something else.
You know that?

202
00:11:37,940 --> 00:11:41,170
I dragged you in here to avoid
a scene in front of the neighbors,

203
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,440
and what do you do?
You puke all over me and pass out.

204
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:46,340
Then you wake up and slap me twice.
Seriously!

205
00:11:46,410 --> 00:11:47,610
Whatever. Forget it.

206
00:11:48,950 --> 00:11:51,350
It's in the past,
so let's just forget about it.

207
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:55,390
Forget it?
How am I supposed to forget that?

208
00:11:55,450 --> 00:11:58,390
- We won't see each other again.
- Hey.

209
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:02,030
Here. For the motel, food,
and drinks. Let's split it.

210
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,460
Good luck with your move.

211
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:07,100
- Let's never meet again. Goodbye.
- Wait a second.

212
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:09,300
- You're short 20 dollars.
- Why, you...

213
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:12,200
Fine, all right. Hey, let's do this.

214
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:16,040
Let's get some hangover soup first.
We can't end things like this.

215
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:18,410
I don't want my last memory of you
to be getting slapped in the face.

216
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,950
- I'm not okay with that.
- Are you crazy?

217
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:22,580
- Come on, just for some soup...
- Gosh, get out of my way!

218
00:12:22,650 --> 00:12:26,850
No, let's at least get soup first.
Dong Suk! Hey... Dong Suk!

219
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:29,350
Dong Suk! Wait up!

220
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:34,090
Look! There just happens to be
a CCTV camera over there.

221
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,790
We should just have to check
the footage from that.

222
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:38,400
If you're going to eat,
you must pay.

223
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:40,430
Don't order food if you can't pay.

224
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:42,130
These jerks...

225
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:45,170
Maybe they were just drunk
and forgot to pay?

226
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:48,610
- Always the optimist, aren't you?
- Dong Suk.

227
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:50,110
Please...

228
00:12:53,780 --> 00:12:54,780
Dong Suk!

229
00:12:55,410 --> 00:12:57,920
Hey! Let's get something to eat
for that hangover.

230
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:05,720
(Motel M)

231
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:13,400
I'm sure this is a bit of a shock.

232
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:17,100
Yes, this isn't what I expected.
It's a little awkward.

233
00:13:17,170 --> 00:13:19,640
It's just that we...

234
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,440
The process...
The legal proceedings...

235
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,610
aren't finalized yet, but anyway,

236
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:26,140
our divorce is
basically a done deal,

237
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,550
so please don't get the wrong idea.
This isn't an affair.

238
00:13:28,650 --> 00:13:32,320
Right. Of course.
It's not like you broke any laws.

239
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:35,890
To explain... We'll never
see each other again, so...

240
00:13:36,390 --> 00:13:39,090
To celebrate my move,
we had a farewell drink and...

241
00:13:44,430 --> 00:13:45,730
I'll be on my way now.

242
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:52,140
- Dong Suk!
- A farewell drink before his move?

243
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:56,210
- He must not know he's not moving.
- Yes, it seems that way.

244
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:59,010
They'll keep seeing
each other around. How awkward.

245
00:13:59,780 --> 00:14:02,880
Gosh, and I can't even tell him.
This is so frustrating.

246
00:14:04,950 --> 00:14:07,850
Any idea what happened yesterday,
Mr. Park?

247
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:14,360
I'm sorry, I'm not really sure
what happened yesterday.

248
00:14:14,430 --> 00:14:16,430
Gong Ju Ah went on a blind date.

249
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:20,400
A retaliatory blind date,
a response to Pacu Nacho's own date.

250
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:24,300
Right. But are you saying
that has something to do...

251
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:26,570
with our Fashion Division's future?

252
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:29,370
If Pacu Nacho
and Gong Ju Ah get together,

253
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:33,240
- he won't leave in a year.
- I see.

254
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:35,580
I don't want Pacu Nacho to leave.

255
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:39,380
But the Director went first, right?
I thought that meant...

256
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:41,850
he was over Ju Ah?

257
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:45,190
It was a date he couldn't cancel.
It's nothing to worry about.

258
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:50,960
You and Gong Ju Ah started together.
You're best friends, aren't you?

259
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:54,400
You know all about each other,
from family to your love lives.

260
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:56,270
Yes, that's right.

261
00:14:56,800 --> 00:15:01,470
She was there when my mom passed
and cared for me when I was alone.

262
00:15:01,540 --> 00:15:02,710
She's a very dear friend.

263
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:05,110
I'm jealous.
A friendship like that...

264
00:15:05,810 --> 00:15:08,810
You have Director Yang.

265
00:15:10,050 --> 00:15:13,720
He says he's leaving in a year.
After everything I've done for him.

266
00:15:14,050 --> 00:15:15,150
So ungrateful.

267
00:15:15,850 --> 00:15:18,220
Anyway, there's something
I need to confirm.

268
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:19,720
Mr. Park.

269
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:24,130
Are you faking this friendship
because you have feelings for her?

270
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:29,100
No, I don't see Gong Ju Ah that way.

271
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:31,640
I'm offended.

272
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:35,070
That's what Pacu Nacho said to me.

273
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:41,810
So, will you work with me
to save the Fashion Division?

274
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,180
Of course.

275
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:46,850
So, should I report back to you
on their progress?

276
00:15:47,050 --> 00:15:48,090
Good.

277
00:15:48,690 --> 00:15:50,190
I'll come up with the plan.

278
00:15:58,860 --> 00:16:00,700
Coffee for a hangover?
I haven't seen that in a while.

279
00:16:03,670 --> 00:16:07,770
Hey, you went on a blind date
and didn't get drunk? No way.

280
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:12,040
No. He said he doesn't drink,
so I just had a few by myself.

281
00:16:13,710 --> 00:16:15,650
So you got shot down hard
and drank yourself silly.

282
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:19,050
But...

283
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:23,820
after I got drunk, I stormed
into Director Yang's place.

284
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:28,130
What? Wow, what a go-getter.

285
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:31,330
You're going to save
the Fashion Division.

286
00:16:31,630 --> 00:16:34,030
- Thank you, Gong Ju Ah.
- What?

287
00:16:34,330 --> 00:16:37,200
Hey, so what happened
after you stormed in?

288
00:16:38,370 --> 00:16:40,800
I confronted him. I asked him
after all that talk about liking me,

289
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:42,170
why he'd go on a blind date
with another woman.

290
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,640
You did? Good for you.
And then, what?

291
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:46,840
He thanked me.

292
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,680
Because he missed me,
and I came to see him.

293
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,120
No way!

294
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:57,190
It's working. It's totally working.
What happened next? Was it R-rated?

295
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:00,060
You're crazy.
This guy has totally lost it. Gosh.

296
00:17:00,290 --> 00:17:04,900
What's so crazy about it? Come on,
what happened next? What happened?

297
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,260
Gosh, I don't know. I just...

298
00:17:07,930 --> 00:17:10,670
I just said that
and then ran for it.

299
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:16,740
Wait a minute. Hey.

300
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:20,380
Then he will definitely
ask you out today.

301
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,550
I guess he might.

302
00:17:36,490 --> 00:17:37,830
(Yang Hyun Bin, Managing Director)

303
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:55,480
Gosh. How old are you, Gong Ju Ah?
Getting your hopes up like this.

304
00:17:59,950 --> 00:18:03,890
I'm taking the morning off.
I'll review the presentation later.

305
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,260
What's this?

306
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:10,090
I thought he didn't want to keep me
updated on every little thing.

307
00:18:10,290 --> 00:18:14,360
Now, he's reporting his schedule?
What's that about?

308
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:24,780
I must've been out of my mind.

309
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,850
How much did I drink?

310
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,450
Gosh, my head.

311
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:41,120
Yes, Vice President.

312
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:42,960
Are you home?

313
00:18:43,430 --> 00:18:46,600
- Yes. I drank too much. Sorry.
- With who?

314
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:49,170
By myself.

315
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:53,500
Why are you keeping secrets from me?
That hurts.

316
00:18:55,110 --> 00:18:57,110
What's that supposed to mean?

317
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:01,910
I heard Ju Ah's date was a bust
and that she went to your place.

318
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:03,680
What?

319
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:09,020
What is that supposed to mean?

320
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:11,190
You're going to keep this a secret
from me?

321
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,920
That's really low of you.

322
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:16,890
Hold on. Just hang up.
We'll talk at the office.

323
00:19:21,470 --> 00:19:23,170
She was here?

324
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,600
Wait, why can't I remember?

325
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:35,780
How could you be so mean? You jerk!

326
00:19:43,850 --> 00:19:46,760
So she was here. It did happen.

327
00:19:53,230 --> 00:19:55,630
But why would she barge in here
and cause a scene?

328
00:19:56,270 --> 00:19:57,900
Her own blind date was a disaster.

329
00:19:58,770 --> 00:20:00,240
She had that coming, but...

330
00:20:02,170 --> 00:20:06,680
Wait. But how did the VP find out?

331
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:11,050
Don't tell me...
Gong Ju Ah told her herself?

332
00:20:18,620 --> 00:20:19,690
Wait a second.

333
00:20:21,430 --> 00:20:23,690
I'm sure I ate gopchang last night,

334
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:28,200
so why do I taste pork belly
on my lips?

335
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:31,130
It can't be.

336
00:20:34,910 --> 00:20:37,610
Is there something wrong
with my taste buds?

337
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:43,410
Ms. Gong.

338
00:20:43,650 --> 00:20:46,150
I heard you drank a ton by yourself
at your blind date yesterday.

339
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:50,620
- Hey!
- Sorry, he kept asking about it.

340
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:55,060
My brother is a total gym rat.
He must've been so boring, right?

341
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:57,090
No, not at all.

342
00:20:57,290 --> 00:21:01,100
He just seemed like
a really healthy guy.

343
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:04,870
My brother said he wanted
to see you again, though.

344
00:21:06,070 --> 00:21:08,910
But only if you quit drinking
and work out with him.

345
00:21:08,970 --> 00:21:10,470
Will you cut it out already?

346
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,950
Right. And pigs will fly.
How can Ju Ah quit drinking?

347
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:21,490
Oh, my.

348
00:21:21,490 --> 00:21:23,890
Those two are such lovebirds now,
and they're not even hiding it.

349
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:27,760
What? Are they together?

350
00:21:28,030 --> 00:21:29,460
Since when?
Was I the only one who didn't know?

351
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:31,630
They went public
in the office a few days ago.

352
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:35,100
They'd liked each other for a while,
but neither had the guts to confess.

353
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,740
So how did they
finally get together?

354
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,970
Apparently, Bo Mi got drunk,

355
00:21:41,970 --> 00:21:44,880
crashed at Se Hyun's,
and kissed him.

356
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:54,790
But isn't it kind of awkward
to date someone at work?

357
00:21:54,850 --> 00:21:57,450
And being the talk of the office
must be weird, too.

358
00:21:59,690 --> 00:22:02,490
I think it would be great.
You'd have synergy.

359
00:22:03,060 --> 00:22:05,630
Exactly. When you're together
in a jungle like this,

360
00:22:06,030 --> 00:22:07,800
you have that emotional support.

361
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:10,300
Even when work's busy,
you can still see each other.

362
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,000
Work and love, all in one spot.

363
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:16,870
What do you say, Sunfish?
Want to go out with me?

364
00:22:17,870 --> 00:22:19,780
What is this Anteater saying?
So annoying!

365
00:22:20,140 --> 00:22:21,210
Seriously.

366
00:22:21,710 --> 00:22:23,680
Why not? Let's do it!

367
00:22:29,450 --> 00:22:34,120
Hey. If you don't want the gossip,
just keep it a secret.

368
00:22:34,290 --> 00:22:37,330
Just announce it before the wedding,
with invitations in hand.

369
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:41,400
Seriously.
Don't get so ahead of yourself!

370
00:22:41,830 --> 00:22:42,900
Honestly...

371
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:55,050
Director Yang, you're here.

372
00:22:56,950 --> 00:22:58,350
Oh, Ms. Gong.

373
00:22:59,220 --> 00:23:01,690
I see you made it home
all right last night.

374
00:23:02,190 --> 00:23:06,520
Yes. No matter how drunk I get,
I can always find my way home.

375
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:08,490
That's a relief.

376
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,000
So, that's all you have...

377
00:23:12,730 --> 00:23:14,060
to say to me?

378
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,500
Is there something else
I should be saying?

379
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:20,600
You don't have to say
anything else, but...

380
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:24,640
I'm just a little thrown off...

381
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,040
since this isn't what I expected.

382
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:28,210
By any chance,

383
00:23:29,110 --> 00:23:32,250
did you happen to black out
from drinking last night?

384
00:23:33,250 --> 00:23:37,250
What do you mean by that?
I was drunk, but...

385
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:40,890
I remember everything.

386
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,930
In that case,
you should apologize to me.

387
00:23:46,730 --> 00:23:50,400
Apologize?
You want me to apologize to you?

388
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:52,600
Isn't that obvious?
You were out of line.

389
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:56,710
I was out of line?
You're saying I was out of line?

390
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:59,740
Am I wrong? I was enjoying
my drink alone when you accosted me.

391
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:01,850
Excuse me, "accosted?"

392
00:24:02,310 --> 00:24:05,820
You came over, kicked my door,
swore at me, and shoved me.

393
00:24:05,820 --> 00:24:07,380
You don't call that being accosted?

394
00:24:08,890 --> 00:24:10,290
Director Yang, could it be...

395
00:24:10,990 --> 00:24:15,230
- Did you drink a lot last night?
- I did. Why do you ask?

396
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:21,300
So, are you saying...

397
00:24:21,770 --> 00:24:25,840
that you only remember me
swearing and shoving you?

398
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:27,970
Was there something else?

399
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:29,840
Director Yang...

400
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:35,310
You're not pretending
to have forgotten, are you?

401
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:39,520
Why would I pretend not to remember?
I remember everything.

402
00:24:39,550 --> 00:24:44,020
I don't black out or do dumb things
just because I've been drinking.

403
00:24:44,090 --> 00:24:45,090
Unbelievable.

404
00:24:45,590 --> 00:24:46,720
I see.

405
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:51,090
Then,
about what happened yesterday...

406
00:24:51,630 --> 00:24:53,100
I'm sorry.

407
00:24:54,330 --> 00:24:57,000
Okay. Apology accepted.

408
00:24:57,070 --> 00:24:58,470
I'll forget about
what happened last night.

409
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:02,970
Next time you have something to say,
do it when you're sober.

410
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:04,370
Got it?

411
00:25:07,180 --> 00:25:09,250
- Okay.
- All right.

412
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:18,090
Here, open up.

413
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:21,320
- No, I can eat it myself.
- I can manage, really.

414
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:24,690
You'll get your hands dirty.
Your hands are too precious.

415
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:26,700
Father, here.

416
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,070
Here, honey, you too.

417
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:34,140
Hyun Bin would throw a fit
if he saw this.

418
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:37,940
He's not here, so who cares?
No one's watching, so let me do it.

419
00:25:38,940 --> 00:25:40,940
Father, how about
webfoot octopus for dinner?

420
00:25:41,410 --> 00:25:44,980
- Sounds good.
- We need more seaweed. I'll get it.

421
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,420
About Jeong Han not moving out...

422
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:55,230
- When will you tell Se Ri?
- Tomorrow.

423
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:58,260
Just tell her soon.
Don't let her find out another way.

424
00:25:58,460 --> 00:26:00,800
I'll handle it, so don't you worry.

425
00:26:01,700 --> 00:26:03,070
Father, honey.

426
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:06,940
How about
webfoot octopus shabu-shabu, then?

427
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:09,170
- Yes! That'd be great.
- That sounds perfect.

428
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:11,740
Then I'd better call Hyun Bin
and tell him to come.

429
00:26:20,180 --> 00:26:24,190
Isn't Director Yang just awful?
How could my kiss be so bad...

430
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:25,560
for him not to even remember it?

431
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:28,560
It's not like he has
selective amnesia or something.

432
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:31,160
How could he forget
just that one thing?

433
00:26:33,230 --> 00:26:37,230
You have my deepest sympathies.

434
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:38,870
Why, you...

435
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:43,240
What am I supposed to do now?

436
00:26:43,710 --> 00:26:46,680
Should I pretend nothing happened?
Just drop it?

437
00:26:46,740 --> 00:26:50,950
- Don't drop it. Make him remember.
- How?

438
00:26:51,820 --> 00:26:53,180
No way.
I could never bring it up myself.

439
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:57,190
Let's use
the Memory Recall Induction Method.

440
00:26:57,890 --> 00:27:00,220
What?
The Memory Recall Induction Method?

441
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:02,630
What's that?

442
00:27:08,300 --> 00:27:11,900
We'll use a visual stimulus
to try and jog his memory.

443
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:43,770
- Hey!
- What? You don't think it'll work?

444
00:27:44,930 --> 00:27:47,740
I can't do that. Gosh, seriously.

445
00:27:48,710 --> 00:27:51,570
Then how about "awakening" therapy?

446
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:53,410
And what's that?

447
00:27:54,010 --> 00:27:57,850
It activates the memory circuits
through a startling response.

448
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,320
What the...

449
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:07,920
You think that'll work?

450
00:28:09,030 --> 00:28:12,800
You've got nothing to lose.
You never know.

451
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:16,900
I'd rather just give him
a good whack on the head.

452
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:19,700
Shock therapy!

453
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:21,500
I like that idea.

454
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:37,690
Forget it. How could I hit him?

455
00:28:37,750 --> 00:28:41,720
- If you can't do it, I can.
- Hey, do you want to get fired?

456
00:28:44,830 --> 00:28:47,960
Hey, I know someone.
Someone who could smack him...

457
00:28:48,030 --> 00:28:49,230
and get away with it.

458
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,000
Who?

459
00:28:56,740 --> 00:29:00,580
- Why did you hit me?
- Shock therapy. Don't you remember?

460
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:03,610
- What am I not remembering?
- Come on.

461
00:29:04,150 --> 00:29:07,380
- How much did you have to drink?
- Did you just hit me for drinking?

462
00:29:07,450 --> 00:29:11,150
- It's because you don't remember.
- But what is it I don't remember?

463
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:14,090
You said you just remember Ju Ah
coming and cursing you out.

464
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:15,760
How did you know that?

465
00:29:16,590 --> 00:29:19,760
- What, are you watching me on CCTV?
- Does that really matter right now?

466
00:29:19,860 --> 00:29:21,460
Then what does?

467
00:29:22,830 --> 00:29:26,170
When Gong Ju Ah
went to your place last night,

468
00:29:27,340 --> 00:29:30,540
- she didn't just curse you out.
- Then what else did she do?

469
00:29:31,340 --> 00:29:32,740
I can't bring myself to say it.

470
00:29:33,380 --> 00:29:35,550
You have to remember it yourself.
Got it?

471
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:43,390
What am I supposed to remember?
This is ridiculous.

472
00:29:47,690 --> 00:29:51,430
I'm asking you.
What happened last night?

473
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:52,960
And why was your phone turned off?

474
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:55,570
I already told you.
Nothing happened.

475
00:29:55,730 --> 00:29:57,670
I was just with a friend.

476
00:29:59,170 --> 00:30:01,100
And did you check out the space
for the shop?

477
00:30:01,470 --> 00:30:02,470
The shop?

478
00:30:03,940 --> 00:30:04,940
The shop, right.

479
00:30:05,980 --> 00:30:09,550
I checked out a restaurant,
but it was just okay.

480
00:30:11,110 --> 00:30:12,120
Dong Suk.

481
00:30:13,320 --> 00:30:14,720
You were with a man last night,
weren't you?

482
00:30:15,690 --> 00:30:18,350
Why?
Did one of the neighbors see me?

483
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:21,360
Did they see me get drunk, pass out,
or go into a motel?

484
00:30:22,560 --> 00:30:24,830
- You did that?
- No, I didn't.

485
00:30:24,890 --> 00:30:26,300
So you did!

486
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:29,500
My gosh, why are you grilling me?

487
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:33,740
Who was it?
It wasn't Ji Hu's dad, was it?

488
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:36,140
No! Do you think I'm crazy enough
to be with that guy?

489
00:30:36,210 --> 00:30:38,940
Exactly. So who was it?

490
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:42,580
Don't ask.
I'm never going to see him again.

491
00:30:42,650 --> 00:30:44,010
Why not?

492
00:30:45,350 --> 00:30:47,750
You didn't just meet him yesterday.
Oh, my goodness.

493
00:30:47,820 --> 00:30:48,820
A one-night stand?

494
00:30:49,450 --> 00:30:51,720
Seriously, keep your voice down.
Someone might hear.

495
00:30:51,790 --> 00:30:53,660
I'm not even divorced yet.

496
00:30:54,290 --> 00:30:58,960
What's the difference?
You're single now, you should date.

497
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:03,370
Oh, my gosh.
You're unbelievable, you know that?

498
00:31:05,470 --> 00:31:07,470
I don't think I'm the one
you're smiling about.

499
00:31:08,100 --> 00:31:10,170
Who could it be? Who is it?

500
00:31:10,970 --> 00:31:12,610
I'm telling you, it's nothing.

501
00:31:13,740 --> 00:31:15,280
Something's fishy.

502
00:31:20,220 --> 00:31:21,320
Hey.

503
00:31:21,750 --> 00:31:23,920
Where did you sleep last night
after you were out drinking?

504
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:26,790
At the spa. I slept at the spa.

505
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:30,560
Why, Mom? Did the police officers
say something?

506
00:31:31,130 --> 00:31:33,060
Why are you bringing up the police?

507
00:31:33,830 --> 00:31:35,270
Did you get into
some kind of trouble?

508
00:31:35,870 --> 00:31:40,700
No, what trouble?
No! I was just asking.

509
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:42,140
Yes, welcome.

510
00:31:42,870 --> 00:31:44,640
My goodness, Mi Hyang.

511
00:31:45,310 --> 00:31:49,010
Hello, there. I was so shocked.

512
00:31:49,450 --> 00:31:53,180
I heard you're closing and moving.
Why is that?

513
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:58,290
I've been doing it for so long,
and I want to get some rest.

514
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,220
I see.

515
00:32:01,060 --> 00:32:02,630
It has been a long time,
that's for sure.

516
00:32:03,330 --> 00:32:06,300
Listen, I have some medicine
that's about to expire,

517
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:10,870
so I packed some for you.
They're hard to sell, so I called.

518
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:14,970
I was just about to stop by
and get some, anyway.

519
00:32:15,670 --> 00:32:17,810
You'll find some fever reducer,
stomach medicine,

520
00:32:17,810 --> 00:32:20,410
and some ointment.
I put in a bunch of things.

521
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:23,250
I also wrote down the instructions
and put the note inside.

522
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:25,650
You're giving me all of this?

523
00:32:26,620 --> 00:32:29,750
Oh, right.
How is your brother's knee?

524
00:32:30,220 --> 00:32:33,520
It's about the same.
At his age, it can't be helped.

525
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:36,130
This is for you.

526
00:32:37,030 --> 00:32:40,700
I made this for you.
I thought it'd suit you.

527
00:32:41,500 --> 00:32:45,400
I've told you time and again
not to do this. Oh, my...

528
00:32:45,470 --> 00:32:49,640
My gosh.
Oh, this is adorable, isn't it?

529
00:32:52,310 --> 00:32:55,410
Oh, that's...
That's the cardigan you always wear.

530
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:58,720
- Oh, so she made that for you?
- Yes.

531
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:03,050
Oh, it wasn't me.
My brother does most of the work.

532
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:06,520
Oh, right. But I don't think
I've ever seen you at the clinic.

533
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:08,120
Anyway, it's nice to meet you.

534
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:10,560
You're the second son, right?

535
00:33:11,860 --> 00:33:14,730
I've seen you around plenty.
You married late,

536
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:16,430
and you don't have any kids.
Am I right?

537
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:19,040
Yes, that's right.

538
00:33:20,240 --> 00:33:23,470
You all look so much alike.

539
00:33:25,310 --> 00:33:27,180
Who does he look like? Me?

540
00:33:27,510 --> 00:33:28,510
Pardon?

541
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:32,750
Oh, yes. He looks like you,

542
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:36,050
and he looks like the doctor.
You all look alike.

543
00:33:36,820 --> 00:33:38,220
Oh, one last thing.

544
00:33:38,490 --> 00:33:41,260
Even after you move,
would it be okay to keep in touch?

545
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:45,430
Oh, of course. Let's keep in touch.

546
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:46,500
Okay.

547
00:33:46,930 --> 00:33:49,800
- I'll be in touch then.
- Please do.

548
00:33:49,870 --> 00:33:51,730
- Okay.
- Take care.

549
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:58,670
Wait, if her brother is that sick,
he should get a prescription.

550
00:33:58,740 --> 00:33:59,910
Why only buy
over-the-counter medicine?

551
00:34:01,580 --> 00:34:03,280
He doesn't have health insurance.

552
00:34:03,650 --> 00:34:05,150
No health insurance at all?

553
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:08,150
That's right. She's been coming
to our pharmacy for...

554
00:34:08,220 --> 00:34:10,150
I'd say almost 30 years?

555
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:14,790
Is he running from debt collectors?
Or is he some kind of fugitive?

556
00:34:14,790 --> 00:34:16,930
Many people had stories like that
back in the day.

557
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:19,300
I'm sure he has his reasons.
You know?

558
00:34:30,470 --> 00:34:33,710
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Treating Patients With Love)

559
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:47,020
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

560
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:59,200
My goodness. Oh, no!

561
00:34:59,270 --> 00:35:02,040
Sir, can you hear me?

562
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:04,770
Sir! Try to open your eyes. Sir...

563
00:35:05,310 --> 00:35:07,240
Hey, someone up front,
please call 911!

564
00:35:07,310 --> 00:35:08,680
- Yes, I'm on it!
- Call 911!

565
00:35:09,150 --> 00:35:10,610
- Hello?
- Sir?

566
00:35:10,680 --> 00:35:13,950
Yes, we're at Onjeong Market.
Oh, a man has collapsed.

567
00:35:14,020 --> 00:35:17,390
Please hurry! Yes?
Please, just get here quickly!

568
00:35:18,750 --> 00:35:19,890
Here, I'll do it.

569
00:35:22,630 --> 00:35:23,690
I'll secure his airway.

570
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:27,830
He's cyanotic.

571
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:29,930
Acute myocardial infarction?

572
00:35:30,030 --> 00:35:33,870
Does anyone know where an AED is?
A defibrillator?

573
00:35:38,610 --> 00:35:42,180
- Oh, thank goodness.
- Sir! Sir, are you with me?

574
00:35:42,310 --> 00:35:44,050
- He's alive!
- He made it.

575
00:35:44,110 --> 00:35:47,250
- Oh, thank goodness, he's alive.
- Really? My gosh.

576
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:50,520
Thank you. Thank you so much.

577
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,520
You're absolutely the best.

578
00:35:57,430 --> 00:35:58,490
Are you okay?

579
00:35:58,930 --> 00:36:01,430
- Are you okay?
- Sir, paramedics will be here soon.

580
00:36:05,070 --> 00:36:06,540
Oh, this...

581
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,710
- I really thought he was a goner.
- But he's alive.

582
00:36:27,190 --> 00:36:29,160
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

583
00:36:31,260 --> 00:36:35,970
Woo Jae, what's going on?
You didn't have to treat me.

584
00:36:36,330 --> 00:36:37,600
I'm so touched.

585
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,640
Because I won't see you
after I move.

586
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:43,340
What? You're planning never to
see me again after you move?

587
00:36:43,770 --> 00:36:46,840
I just meant we won't see each other
as often as we do now.

588
00:36:47,540 --> 00:36:52,480
Don't tell me you'd ghost me
without saying where you're moving.

589
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:54,220
Of course not.

590
00:36:54,580 --> 00:36:57,120
Even if I tried,
you'd hunt me down somehow.

591
00:36:58,090 --> 00:37:00,890
See? You know me so well now.

592
00:37:02,190 --> 00:37:05,060
Hey, guess what?
I'm getting start-up funds from Dad.

593
00:37:05,700 --> 00:37:09,230
I'll buy cameras, lights, and gear,
and I'll lease a studio too.

594
00:37:09,570 --> 00:37:10,700
What are you going to do with it?

595
00:37:11,070 --> 00:37:13,900
I want to be a content creator
who reviews fashion brands.

596
00:37:14,700 --> 00:37:16,670
Yes, I think you'd be good at that.

597
00:37:19,340 --> 00:37:20,940
But that start-up money...

598
00:37:21,210 --> 00:37:23,910
It's my reward for scheming
to stop your family from moving.

599
00:37:25,210 --> 00:37:29,790
- What are you talking about?
- Your family isn't moving anymore.

600
00:37:30,650 --> 00:37:31,990
We won't be separated.

601
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:36,260
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

602
00:37:36,490 --> 00:37:38,030
- We need to talk.
- What?

603
00:37:38,090 --> 00:37:39,100
- Come on.
- Hey.

604
00:37:39,430 --> 00:37:42,160
Hey, what's gotten into you?
Seriously? Hey.

605
00:37:44,630 --> 00:37:47,100
What's this about
the dads agreeing not to move?

606
00:37:47,740 --> 00:37:50,410
What do you mean you're not moving
and going on "Human Theater?"

607
00:37:50,570 --> 00:37:52,070
How did you find that out?

608
00:37:52,340 --> 00:37:54,480
- Who told you?
- Eun Bin.

609
00:37:55,110 --> 00:37:57,410
Hey, your mom doesn't know,
does she?

610
00:37:57,980 --> 00:38:01,280
If you're so scared, why start this?
You think you won't get caught?

611
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:05,660
Go tell them right now.
Tell them the move is still on.

612
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,720
Hey, let go of me! My goodness!

613
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:11,430
Hey! Look, Woo Jae.
I'm going to tell your mom tomorrow,

614
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:14,530
and if she really says no,
I swear I won't do it, okay?

615
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:16,330
So don't worry about it, okay?

616
00:38:16,630 --> 00:38:19,140
Do you think she'll say yes?
You really don't know her, do you?

617
00:38:19,770 --> 00:38:22,640
You're right.
She'll probably say no.

618
00:38:23,270 --> 00:38:25,270
Even so,
I should at least tell her...

619
00:38:25,340 --> 00:38:28,240
But if it's a no-go anyway,
why even bother telling her?

620
00:38:29,080 --> 00:38:32,150
Come on, you two just made up.
Are you really going to do this?

621
00:38:32,780 --> 00:38:35,180
When you two were separated
and Mom was living alone, I...

622
00:38:35,420 --> 00:38:37,950
I was... It was so hard for me.

623
00:38:38,220 --> 00:38:40,220
But Dad,
if you stir things up again...

624
00:38:40,490 --> 00:38:43,060
You'll... You'll just upset Mom...

625
00:38:46,060 --> 00:38:50,930
Hey, what's wrong, Gong Woo Jae?
Woo Jae, what's happening to you?

626
00:38:51,100 --> 00:38:54,570
Hold your breath.
Now, breathe slowly. Slowly, okay?

627
00:38:55,300 --> 00:38:56,940
Yes, that's it. Slowly.

628
00:38:57,670 --> 00:38:59,080
Yes, slowly...

629
00:39:00,940 --> 00:39:02,080
I'm okay.

630
00:39:02,650 --> 00:39:06,680
Hey, is your heart pounding?
Does your chest feel tight?

631
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:11,120
- Kid, you have to get checked out.
- Dad, I...

632
00:39:11,790 --> 00:39:12,920
What? What is it?

633
00:39:16,730 --> 00:39:18,060
I have an anxiety disorder.

634
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:21,530
I'm taking medication,
so please just keep this between us.

635
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:23,500
Since when?

636
00:39:24,170 --> 00:39:25,200
For a while now.

637
00:39:25,770 --> 00:39:28,100
When I start to feel anxious,
I get short of breath.

638
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,710
But it's not serious,
so please keep it a secret, okay?

639
00:39:32,010 --> 00:39:34,380
Hey, you punk!
This isn't something to keep secret!

640
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:36,110
Please, just don't tell Mom. Please?

641
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:38,780
Dad, please.
I'm seriously begging you, okay?

642
00:39:38,850 --> 00:39:41,120
Dad, Mom can't find out about this.

643
00:39:41,380 --> 00:39:44,120
Okay, all right.

644
00:39:44,190 --> 00:39:47,520
Okay, all right. Calm down.
All right, breathe slowly.

645
00:39:48,360 --> 00:39:50,890
Gosh, this kid, seriously!
Yes, calm down.

646
00:40:05,340 --> 00:40:08,310
What's wrong?
Isn't this enough proof I'm serious?

647
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:10,910
Do we need to add
some other clauses?

648
00:40:12,110 --> 00:40:13,120
I...

649
00:40:13,980 --> 00:40:15,080
don't think I can do it.

650
00:40:15,580 --> 00:40:17,490
Dong Ik, I'm so sorry.

651
00:40:17,950 --> 00:40:19,190
Hey, what gives, President?

652
00:40:19,660 --> 00:40:21,360
I thought we had this
all figured out, right?

653
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,730
I know, but...

654
00:40:24,830 --> 00:40:27,930
I was really tempted,
and I tried to follow through.

655
00:40:28,530 --> 00:40:30,170
But I'm not like you.

656
00:40:30,870 --> 00:40:35,000
Your whole family has your back,
but I'm on my own.

657
00:40:35,670 --> 00:40:38,310
Not a single person in my family
will back me up.

658
00:40:38,770 --> 00:40:41,610
I'll help you, okay?
I'll convince them for you.

659
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:44,950
- Forget it.
- Come on, Jeong Han. Please.

660
00:40:45,450 --> 00:40:49,350
The producer says the deal is signed
and they're coming next week, okay?

661
00:40:49,420 --> 00:40:50,420
Come on.

662
00:40:50,790 --> 00:40:53,820
You'll be fine even if
I don't go on the show with you.

663
00:40:54,260 --> 00:40:58,030
Just do what your wife tells you,
and you'll be fine, got it?

664
00:40:58,430 --> 00:41:00,700
No. Over my dead body. You can't go.

665
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:03,500
Hey, let go! Let go of me!

666
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:14,910
(What in the world happened?
I can't remember. It's a blank.)

667
00:41:18,950 --> 00:41:22,020
- I'm heading out now.
- Ms. Gong.

668
00:41:23,090 --> 00:41:27,560
I'm honestly not sure
what I'm supposed to be remembering.

669
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:31,260
If I made a mistake,
I'm truly sorry.

670
00:41:33,530 --> 00:41:35,200
We kissed, Director.

671
00:41:36,170 --> 00:41:39,340
- What?
- I said, we kissed.

672
00:41:42,470 --> 00:41:45,270
Come on, stop joking around.

673
00:41:45,570 --> 00:41:48,280
You really think I'd kiss someone
and then not remember it?

674
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:50,810
And if we had, that would have been
our first kiss.

675
00:41:51,150 --> 00:41:52,950
How could I possibly forget that?

676
00:41:53,620 --> 00:41:54,650
Good question.

677
00:41:55,990 --> 00:41:57,420
It was our first kiss.

678
00:42:01,020 --> 00:42:03,230
I'll be on my way.

679
00:42:04,330 --> 00:42:05,330
Wait a second.

680
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:09,600
Hi, Grandma.

681
00:42:10,330 --> 00:42:11,330
Lettuce? On my way home?

682
00:42:12,470 --> 00:42:14,100
Are we having pork belly
for dinner tonight?

683
00:42:15,070 --> 00:42:16,640
But I had pork belly yesterday, too.

684
00:42:17,670 --> 00:42:19,980
Okay, fine.

685
00:42:20,510 --> 00:42:21,510
Yes.

686
00:42:22,750 --> 00:42:24,210
"Pork belly yesterday, too."

687
00:42:25,810 --> 00:42:27,780
Wait, because we kissed yesterday...

688
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:30,850
Is that why my lips
tasted like pork belly?

689
00:42:32,890 --> 00:42:33,890
Man...

690
00:42:36,990 --> 00:42:40,460
I can't just pretend to remember.

691
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:43,430
Gosh, why can't I remember?

692
00:42:44,630 --> 00:42:46,870
You fool!

693
00:42:55,910 --> 00:42:57,210
No matter how hard I think,

694
00:42:57,810 --> 00:43:01,050
I can't remember how we ended up
sleeping in the same bed.

695
00:43:06,820 --> 00:43:07,920
Gosh, my back.

696
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:12,290
I must buy a bed this year.
Sleeping on the floor at my age...

697
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:13,360
is going to break my back.

698
00:43:15,730 --> 00:43:16,800
A bed?

699
00:43:17,200 --> 00:43:19,870
- The floor?
- You should sleep on the bed.

700
00:43:20,570 --> 00:43:21,870
Why are you sleeping on the floor?

701
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:24,040
Oh, boy...

702
00:43:24,810 --> 00:43:26,340
She threw up all over my clothes.
Darn it.

703
00:43:30,180 --> 00:43:31,180
Gosh, gross.

704
00:43:31,680 --> 00:43:33,680
The smell won't go away. Seriously.

705
00:43:34,220 --> 00:43:35,280
What the heck did she eat?

706
00:43:36,450 --> 00:43:39,250
You should sleep on the bed.
Why are you sleeping on the floor?

707
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:42,090
Good grief.

708
00:43:42,420 --> 00:43:47,300
Hey, it's bad for circulation
to sleep in socks this tight.

709
00:43:48,830 --> 00:43:49,930
Go away.

710
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:52,900
I'm such a mess.

711
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:54,800
What do you mean, a mess?
You're not.

712
00:43:55,870 --> 00:43:58,340
Get some more sleep.
I'll get going now.

713
00:44:01,180 --> 00:44:02,380
Don't go.

714
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:05,850
I'm scared to be by myself.

715
00:44:08,480 --> 00:44:09,490
All right.

716
00:44:11,150 --> 00:44:12,150
I'll stay here.

717
00:44:12,890 --> 00:44:13,890
Now, sleep.

718
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:23,070
Water...

719
00:44:23,830 --> 00:44:25,130
Water...

720
00:44:38,550 --> 00:44:39,550
Darn it.

721
00:45:14,380 --> 00:45:15,950
It's all coming back to me now.

722
00:45:18,450 --> 00:45:19,760
Don't kid yourself, Yang Dong Suk.

723
00:45:20,190 --> 00:45:23,030
He's just a nice guy.
It doesn't mean he likes you.

724
00:45:24,490 --> 00:45:27,000
He was just taking pity on you,
like you were a lost puppy.

725
00:45:37,010 --> 00:45:38,010
Oh, my.

726
00:45:38,870 --> 00:45:40,710
Wow, this motel's laundry detergent
is really good.

727
00:45:41,780 --> 00:45:42,910
It left a really nice scent.

728
00:45:54,420 --> 00:45:56,960
Why am I thinking about this?
Gong Dae Han, are you crazy?

729
00:45:57,760 --> 00:45:58,760
You're supposed to forget her.

730
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:00,900
You'll never see each other again.

731
00:46:01,530 --> 00:46:02,630
It can never happen between you two.

732
00:46:03,170 --> 00:46:04,170
Got it?

733
00:46:13,510 --> 00:46:15,540
(Passenger Use Only,
15-Person Capacity)

734
00:46:45,470 --> 00:46:46,480
- Oh, no.
- My gosh.

735
00:46:46,780 --> 00:46:47,780
Goodness.

736
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:51,710
- Seriously? How could you do this?
- What?

737
00:47:05,130 --> 00:47:06,130
Right.

738
00:47:06,500 --> 00:47:07,930
I was the one
who brought her inside.

739
00:47:14,500 --> 00:47:15,500
Where did we go after that?

740
00:47:16,540 --> 00:47:18,810
Did we come in and drink together?

741
00:47:19,470 --> 00:47:22,110
Yes. So what if I have? You jerk.

742
00:47:24,180 --> 00:47:25,180
What's so funny?

743
00:47:26,080 --> 00:47:27,080
Because I'm grateful.

744
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:28,850
I missed you so much,

745
00:47:29,380 --> 00:47:31,790
and here you are. I'm just so happy.

746
00:48:09,630 --> 00:48:11,230
Why are you here?

747
00:48:12,430 --> 00:48:13,530
I remember now.

748
00:48:14,630 --> 00:48:17,470
I remember everything now.

749
00:48:25,270 --> 00:48:26,280
I'm sorry.

750
00:48:27,110 --> 00:48:28,280
You were really hurt, weren't you?

751
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:30,810
You're unbelievable.

752
00:48:34,350 --> 00:48:36,220
Forget everything about yesterday.

753
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:40,590
Because this is our first kiss.

754
00:49:08,950 --> 00:49:09,950
Yes, Director Song.

755
00:49:10,650 --> 00:49:12,020
I'm just heading home from work.

756
00:49:13,090 --> 00:49:17,890
Gosh, just thinking about moving
makes my commute feel much longer.

757
00:49:18,560 --> 00:49:21,330
By the way, Seong Mi.
You guys are still moving, right?

758
00:49:22,260 --> 00:49:23,430
Yes, we are. Why?

759
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:27,800
Well, a junior producer was pitching
an interesting idea,

760
00:49:27,870 --> 00:49:30,010
and it was about
Jeong Han and Dong Ik.

761
00:49:31,070 --> 00:49:32,940
Are you talking about
"Human Theater?"

762
00:49:34,110 --> 00:49:36,610
That's just Yang Dong Ik
doing his own thing.

763
00:49:36,950 --> 00:49:38,250
So you knew.

764
00:49:38,810 --> 00:49:41,220
I thought Jeong Han caused trouble
behind your back again.

765
00:49:41,920 --> 00:49:46,620
Please. Dr. Gong has changed.
He no longer goes behind my back.

766
00:49:47,020 --> 00:49:48,190
Well, that's a relief then.

767
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:50,630
I just heard he even met
with the producer and writer.

768
00:49:51,090 --> 00:49:52,860
Yang Dong Ik
must have met them alone.

769
00:49:53,660 --> 00:49:55,200
Hold on, I'm getting a call.

770
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:57,000
Okay.

771
00:49:58,630 --> 00:50:00,340
Yes, this is Han Seong Mi.

772
00:50:00,740 --> 00:50:01,740
Hey.

773
00:50:08,780 --> 00:50:11,110
This is the first time
it's just been the two of us, right?

774
00:50:12,280 --> 00:50:14,250
Oh, is it?

775
00:50:15,180 --> 00:50:16,220
I don't think so.

776
00:50:17,490 --> 00:50:20,220
- That's not how I remember it.
- Well, as far as I remember, it is.

777
00:50:21,160 --> 00:50:22,160
Anyway,

778
00:50:23,460 --> 00:50:24,460
why did you want to see me?

779
00:50:26,190 --> 00:50:27,330
Well...

780
00:50:29,330 --> 00:50:31,370
The thing is, I...

781
00:50:32,570 --> 00:50:33,700
The reason
I asked to see you today...

782
00:50:33,800 --> 00:50:36,840
You want to be on "Human Theater?"
To tell us not to move?

783
00:50:37,970 --> 00:50:39,110
So you already know.

784
00:50:39,940 --> 00:50:42,280
The producer and writer
for "Human Theater."

785
00:50:42,910 --> 00:50:45,380
By any chance,
did Dr. Gong meet them too?

786
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:47,980
Yes, we all met together.

787
00:50:49,220 --> 00:50:51,950
- This is unbelievable.
- Hey, Seong Mi.

788
00:50:52,590 --> 00:50:55,090
Jeong Han didn't do anything wrong.
This was all my doing.

789
00:50:55,620 --> 00:50:58,490
It takes two to tango.
He must have been in on it.

790
00:50:58,560 --> 00:51:00,230
No, absolutely not.

791
00:51:01,830 --> 00:51:02,830
Here, look at this.

792
00:51:05,030 --> 00:51:06,030
It's a pledge of devotion.

793
00:51:06,870 --> 00:51:08,570
This is how hard
I had to persuade Jeong Han.

794
00:51:18,380 --> 00:51:20,650
You really wanted to go this far?

795
00:51:20,850 --> 00:51:23,320
Yes. Think about
how badly I must've wanted it...

796
00:51:23,390 --> 00:51:24,890
for me to go to such lengths.

797
00:51:25,550 --> 00:51:28,790
I told the substation chief
to cancel his lease.

798
00:51:28,990 --> 00:51:31,630
And I convinced Mr. Jo
to stay away from the clinic.

799
00:51:31,690 --> 00:51:34,430
Hey! You did what now?

800
00:51:34,730 --> 00:51:36,130
You didn't know about that, did you?

801
00:51:48,010 --> 00:51:49,010
What...

802
00:51:59,960 --> 00:52:02,060
Your wife doesn't know about this,
does she?

803
00:52:02,290 --> 00:52:04,760
No, but everyone else knows.

804
00:52:05,460 --> 00:52:06,460
The rest of the family...

805
00:52:07,130 --> 00:52:09,100
was thrilled you weren't moving.

806
00:52:09,260 --> 00:52:11,800
- Everyone except for your wife?
- Yes.

807
00:52:11,870 --> 00:52:14,870
You have no idea
how much she hates me, do you?

808
00:52:14,940 --> 00:52:16,070
I do. I know, but...

809
00:52:17,040 --> 00:52:20,510
Look, I'll figure out a way
to smooth things over with my wife.

810
00:52:20,880 --> 00:52:22,710
- Don't worry.
- Forget it.

811
00:52:23,010 --> 00:52:26,210
We're still moving,
and we're not doing "Human Theater."

812
00:52:27,080 --> 00:52:28,080
Hey.

813
00:52:28,380 --> 00:52:31,890
That's not the only reason
I wanted to see you.

814
00:52:32,220 --> 00:52:35,760
Look, Jeong Han turned me down
for "Human Theater" anyway.

815
00:52:37,060 --> 00:52:38,560
Then why did you ask to see me?

816
00:52:42,560 --> 00:52:44,130
Seong Mi, the way I see it...

817
00:52:45,270 --> 00:52:47,940
I don't think
Jeong Han wants to move.

818
00:52:48,900 --> 00:52:51,410
He was swayed by what I said
because he doesn't want to move.

819
00:52:52,140 --> 00:52:53,140
Don't you think?

820
00:52:54,010 --> 00:52:55,340
Are you telling me...

821
00:52:56,680 --> 00:52:58,880
that I don't even know
what my own husband wants?

822
00:52:58,950 --> 00:53:00,320
No, of course, you do.

823
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:04,950
Come on, you're like a mind reader.
You're an expert. You know.

824
00:53:05,590 --> 00:53:07,060
That's not what I mean.
What I'm saying is...

825
00:53:07,890 --> 00:53:11,590
Just one more time, okay?
I'm just asking you to reconsider.

826
00:53:12,130 --> 00:53:15,700
Hey, I got rid of every reason
you had to move in the first place.

827
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:16,800
Right?

828
00:53:17,300 --> 00:53:19,970
And if you did "Human Theater,"
I would be so grateful...

829
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:21,040
Hey, Seong Mi!

830
00:53:29,680 --> 00:53:30,680
You startled me.

831
00:53:32,250 --> 00:53:34,680
I need to have a word with you.

832
00:53:41,060 --> 00:53:42,460
Why were you meeting...

833
00:53:43,460 --> 00:53:44,860
with Dr. Yang?

834
00:53:46,260 --> 00:53:50,130
If you're so curious,
ask Dr. Yang Dong Ik yourself.

835
00:53:50,630 --> 00:53:51,800
Ask him what we talked about.

836
00:53:52,230 --> 00:53:53,270
You see,

837
00:53:54,040 --> 00:53:56,570
I'm not asking
what the two of you discussed.

838
00:53:56,940 --> 00:53:58,410
That is not my question.

839
00:53:59,370 --> 00:54:02,940
What I'm asking is
why a married woman...

840
00:54:03,010 --> 00:54:04,680
would meet with another man alone.

841
00:54:05,280 --> 00:54:08,520
Your families are already enemies,
because of an affair.

842
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:09,780
Two affairs, at that.

843
00:54:11,190 --> 00:54:14,760
So shouldn't you two, of all people,
avoid meeting like this?

844
00:54:15,320 --> 00:54:16,660
Especially you two.

845
00:54:17,030 --> 00:54:18,160
Especially us two?

846
00:54:19,430 --> 00:54:21,730
What are you insinuating?

847
00:54:22,600 --> 00:54:24,700
Your actions invite
misunderstanding.

848
00:54:25,670 --> 00:54:28,370
Frankly, Doctor,
that whole thing with your photo...

849
00:54:28,640 --> 00:54:31,610
I think you were just asking
for people to get the wrong idea.

850
00:54:31,770 --> 00:54:35,110
So much for your apology.
You're showing your true colors now.

851
00:54:35,910 --> 00:54:37,010
I'm just saying this...

852
00:54:37,480 --> 00:54:40,050
because I'm worried
about you, Doctor.

853
00:54:40,520 --> 00:54:44,750
Anyone who saw you two today
would start talking.

854
00:54:45,090 --> 00:54:49,260
Please, for your own sake
and for your family,

855
00:54:50,560 --> 00:54:52,830
watch your behavior...

856
00:54:53,530 --> 00:54:56,200
I'd appreciate it
if you were more careful.

857
00:54:58,000 --> 00:54:59,000
I see.

858
00:54:59,700 --> 00:55:01,970
If you've never had to navigate
a professional environment,

859
00:55:02,470 --> 00:55:04,340
I can see how you might
get the wrong idea.

860
00:55:09,410 --> 00:55:11,180
I never had to navigate
a professional environment?

861
00:55:11,710 --> 00:55:14,620
For your information,
I've been through it all.

862
00:55:15,620 --> 00:55:16,650
Okay, fine.

863
00:55:20,060 --> 00:55:22,960
Here. This is the reason Dr. Yang...

864
00:55:23,060 --> 00:55:25,660
asked to see me.

865
00:55:26,800 --> 00:55:28,160
You recognize my husband's
handwriting, don't you?

866
00:55:36,400 --> 00:55:37,670
(Pledge)

867
00:55:37,670 --> 00:55:39,140
"This written pledge..."

868
00:55:39,670 --> 00:55:42,180
"is to thank Gong Jeong Han
for calling off his move..."

869
00:55:42,910 --> 00:55:46,450
"and agreeing to appear
on 'Human Theater' together."

870
00:55:46,880 --> 00:55:49,920
"In return, Yang Dong Ik pledges
his loyalty to Gong Jeong Han."

871
00:55:52,290 --> 00:55:53,620
"This document serves as that oath."

872
00:55:57,490 --> 00:55:58,490
This is...

873
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:01,800
His whole family schemed
to keep us from moving.

874
00:56:03,160 --> 00:56:04,530
Everyone but you.

875
00:56:18,850 --> 00:56:19,850
Dad.

876
00:56:20,320 --> 00:56:21,850
Promise me
you won't say a word tomorrow.

877
00:56:23,950 --> 00:56:24,990
Okay.

878
00:56:25,450 --> 00:56:28,260
I told Bucket I wouldn't,
so don't worry.

879
00:56:28,560 --> 00:56:30,560
And you, make sure
to find the time...

880
00:56:30,830 --> 00:56:32,090
to talk to your mom, okay?

881
00:56:33,060 --> 00:56:34,060
I will.

882
00:56:34,400 --> 00:56:35,400
Hey.

883
00:56:36,260 --> 00:56:37,300
I wonder if the traffic is bad.

884
00:56:37,300 --> 00:56:39,530
- Seong Mi should be home by now.
- I know.

885
00:56:39,600 --> 00:56:40,940
Woo Jae, look at this meat.
It looks amazing.

886
00:56:43,170 --> 00:56:44,210
Ju Ah's late too.

887
00:56:44,710 --> 00:56:45,940
I should've just gotten
the lettuce myself.

888
00:56:47,810 --> 00:56:49,340
- I'm home.
- You're back.

889
00:56:49,410 --> 00:56:50,780
- Seong Mi, you're home.
- Hey, come on in.

890
00:56:50,780 --> 00:56:53,550
Get changed and join us.
We're having pork belly tonight!

891
00:56:53,920 --> 00:56:57,090
Mother, I don't have an appetite,
so I'm just going to rest.

892
00:56:57,190 --> 00:57:00,190
- What? Why?
- What's wrong? Feeling sick?

893
00:57:00,660 --> 00:57:03,560
Come on, we haven't had pork belly
in a while. You should have some.

894
00:57:04,060 --> 00:57:06,590
Cancel our reservation
at Portobelli for tomorrow.

895
00:57:07,130 --> 00:57:08,630
Cancel it? Why?

896
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:12,900
I ran into Bucket on my way home.
I heard about your plan.

897
00:57:13,870 --> 00:57:17,040
What? You... You met Bucket?

898
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:21,640
What?

899
00:57:22,240 --> 00:57:25,280
Hey. What is Seong Mi talking about?

900
00:57:26,010 --> 00:57:27,020
No...

901
00:57:28,280 --> 00:57:29,380
What am I going to do...

902
00:57:33,490 --> 00:57:35,390
- Unbelievable...
- Seong Mi, open the door.

903
00:57:35,460 --> 00:57:37,160
- What is it?
- You've got it all wrong.

904
00:57:37,230 --> 00:57:38,930
What's going on?

905
00:57:39,090 --> 00:57:42,500
Seong Mi, don't listen to Bucket.
You need to hear my side.

906
00:57:43,130 --> 00:57:45,230
Seong Mi, open the door!

907
00:57:45,770 --> 00:57:48,140
Seong Mi, come on, open the door.
Seong Mi!

908
00:57:48,200 --> 00:57:49,640
Seong Mi, the way I see it...

909
00:57:50,440 --> 00:57:51,510
I don't think...

910
00:57:52,210 --> 00:57:53,470
Jeong Han wants to move.

911
00:57:54,210 --> 00:57:56,910
He was swayed by what I said
because he doesn't want to move.

912
00:57:57,550 --> 00:57:58,750
Don't you think?

913
00:57:59,410 --> 00:58:04,220
Seong Mi, please open the door.
You've got this all wrong.

914
00:58:04,620 --> 00:58:06,550
Just listen to me, Seong Mi!

915
00:58:07,290 --> 00:58:09,620
I'm telling you, open the door!
Seong Mi!

916
00:58:12,360 --> 00:58:15,730
His whole family schemed
to keep us from moving.

917
00:58:17,000 --> 00:58:18,400
Everyone but you.

918
00:58:22,140 --> 00:58:23,400
Everyone but me...

919
00:58:27,180 --> 00:58:28,180
Just me...

920
00:58:35,720 --> 00:58:36,950
I'm home, Dad.

921
00:58:38,150 --> 00:58:39,150
What?

922
00:58:42,390 --> 00:58:43,630
It's you, not Se Ri.

923
00:58:44,160 --> 00:58:45,930
Why? Se Ri's not home?

924
00:58:46,390 --> 00:58:48,200
She went to get webfoot octopus,
but she's running late.

925
00:58:49,230 --> 00:58:51,600
I'm starving.
What's taking her so long?

926
00:58:51,830 --> 00:58:54,270
What? You don't have hands?
Go make yourselves useful.

927
00:58:54,340 --> 00:58:57,270
But you know Grandfather
won't eat anything we make.

928
00:58:57,440 --> 00:59:00,310
I'm having the webfoot octopus.
Call Se Ri.

929
00:59:07,650 --> 00:59:09,650
Honey, where are you?

930
00:59:10,390 --> 00:59:12,490
Hurry and get back.
Everyone's starving and complaining.

931
00:59:13,760 --> 00:59:14,760
What am I...

932
00:59:16,760 --> 00:59:18,290
to this family?

933
00:59:19,560 --> 00:59:22,000
- What?
- Am I not part of this family?

934
00:59:23,030 --> 00:59:24,230
Am I still...

935
00:59:25,970 --> 00:59:27,070
just an outsider to you?

936
00:59:28,270 --> 00:59:30,040
What are you talking about?

937
00:59:30,340 --> 00:59:31,340
I...

938
00:59:31,870 --> 00:59:33,840
saw the letter
you wrote to Dr. Gong.

939
00:59:35,980 --> 00:59:39,480
How did you see the letter
I wrote to Jeong Han?

940
00:59:39,910 --> 00:59:41,650
What's going on? She saw the letter?

941
00:59:42,320 --> 00:59:43,750
A letter?
What letter is she talking about?

942
00:59:44,790 --> 00:59:47,520
I was going to explain
everything to you tomorrow.

943
00:59:48,260 --> 00:59:49,290
Just come home for now.

944
00:59:50,390 --> 00:59:52,130
How could you do that
behind my back?

945
00:59:52,860 --> 00:59:54,360
How could you
leave me out of it completely?

946
00:59:55,160 --> 00:59:56,330
Honey, I...

947
00:59:57,400 --> 01:00:00,300
I thought I was doing everything
I could for our family.

948
01:00:02,070 --> 01:00:04,870
Am I standing in the way
of this family's happiness?

949
01:00:06,340 --> 01:00:07,410
Am I no longer...

950
01:00:09,640 --> 01:00:10,680
needed?

951
01:00:11,280 --> 01:00:15,480
Honey, what are you saying?
Of course, that's not true.

952
01:00:15,920 --> 01:00:16,990
Where are you right now?

953
01:00:17,890 --> 01:00:18,890
Hello?

954
01:00:19,520 --> 01:00:21,220
Se Ri? Are you there?

955
01:00:34,270 --> 01:00:37,240
Mom, please come out so we can talk.
Okay?

956
01:00:38,770 --> 01:00:40,980
Mom, you still have to
eat something.

957
01:00:47,080 --> 01:00:49,950
We'll move out.
I promise, Mom, we'll move.

958
01:00:50,280 --> 01:00:52,590
I'll talk to Seong Mi
and make sure she understands.

959
01:00:52,950 --> 01:00:54,360
No, but wait.

960
01:00:54,920 --> 01:00:56,490
The whole thing
with the police substation chief,

961
01:00:56,920 --> 01:00:59,790
with Mr. Jo,
Dong Suk opening her store,

962
01:01:00,190 --> 01:01:01,930
and their grandfather
being involved with the pharmacy...

963
01:01:01,930 --> 01:01:03,060
You knew everything,

964
01:01:03,130 --> 01:01:05,330
but you didn't say a thing to us.
That was pretty messed up of you.

965
01:01:06,700 --> 01:01:07,700
You.

966
01:01:10,270 --> 01:01:11,770
Be honest with me.

967
01:01:12,410 --> 01:01:14,080
If Woo Jae hadn't stepped in,

968
01:01:14,440 --> 01:01:16,780
were you planning to tell Seong Mi
tomorrow...

969
01:01:17,650 --> 01:01:18,780
that you wanted
to call off the move?

970
01:01:23,420 --> 01:01:24,820
You don't have to answer.
I can tell.

971
01:01:25,550 --> 01:01:27,990
No, it's true
I was having second thoughts,

972
01:01:28,660 --> 01:01:31,630
but I don't want to cause Seong Mi
any more trouble.

973
01:01:32,030 --> 01:01:34,560
Even if Woo Jae hadn't stopped me,
I would've come to my senses.

974
01:01:34,800 --> 01:01:36,130
I mean it, Mom.

975
01:01:37,330 --> 01:01:40,030
See, Mom? He said he would've.

976
01:01:40,330 --> 01:01:44,570
So please... Anyway, why did Bucket
say that to Seong Mi?

977
01:01:44,770 --> 01:01:47,940
Was he trying to stir up trouble?
Did he just tattle out of spite?

978
01:01:48,010 --> 01:01:49,010
Just like that, out of spite?

979
01:01:51,550 --> 01:01:52,550
Unbelievable.

980
01:01:56,320 --> 01:01:58,190
Did you get those for me?

981
01:01:59,050 --> 01:02:00,990
I was in a rush,
so this was all I could get.

982
01:02:01,460 --> 01:02:04,130
I felt like
I couldn't let tonight go by.

983
01:02:06,330 --> 01:02:10,260
I wonder if you'll forget about this
by tomorrow morning.

984
01:02:11,530 --> 01:02:13,500
I guess I just gave you
something else to tease me about.

985
01:02:15,370 --> 01:02:18,210
It'll be fun. I'm going to
tease you about this forever.

986
01:02:19,340 --> 01:02:22,510
You will, right?
You'll tease me forever?

987
01:02:24,910 --> 01:02:27,420
Just give me the flowers already.

988
01:02:30,220 --> 01:02:31,720
I finally get to say this.

989
01:02:37,160 --> 01:02:41,360
Go out with me, Gong Ju Ah.
Today is officially our first day.

990
01:02:48,570 --> 01:02:50,200
Our first day.

991
01:02:52,110 --> 01:02:54,080
No matter what happens,
we won't be shaken.

992
01:02:54,740 --> 01:02:55,810
Promise.

993
01:02:58,680 --> 01:02:59,710
Promise.

994
01:03:07,520 --> 01:03:08,820
Once your family moves,

995
01:03:09,560 --> 01:03:11,790
our families won't have a reason
to fight anymore,

996
01:03:12,830 --> 01:03:15,330
and since I'll be working
with your mom,

997
01:03:15,800 --> 01:03:18,100
I'll become
the son-in-law she adores.

998
01:03:20,640 --> 01:03:23,600
I think my mom
already really likes you.

999
01:03:24,540 --> 01:03:26,170
See? I knew it.

1000
01:03:27,680 --> 01:03:31,580
I'll be here all weekend,
so let's get together both days.

1001
01:03:36,120 --> 01:03:40,620
Hello? Se Ri, come on.
Why aren't you picking up? Why?

1002
01:03:40,920 --> 01:03:44,960
Hey, Bucket!
Why didn't you answer my call?

1003
01:03:45,260 --> 01:03:47,760
- What are you doing here?
- You jerk! You really have to ask?

1004
01:03:48,030 --> 01:03:50,100
Why were you meeting with Seong Mi?

1005
01:03:50,260 --> 01:03:53,600
Look, I'm not in my right mind
right now, so just go.

1006
01:03:54,440 --> 01:03:57,810
You jerk! Do I look like
I'm in my right mind?

1007
01:04:28,740 --> 01:04:31,470
(Recipe For Love)

1008
01:04:31,910 --> 01:04:34,680
What shampoo do you use?
Your hair smells great.

1009
01:04:36,340 --> 01:04:40,280
I'm sorry to just show up like this.
I need to ask you a favor.

1010
01:04:40,410 --> 01:04:42,580
The moment you walk in,
you get on your knees. Got it?

1011
01:04:42,750 --> 01:04:45,050
Forgive me just this once, okay?
Seong Mi. Please.

1012
01:04:45,550 --> 01:04:48,060
Tell me why you wavered.

1013
01:04:49,290 --> 01:04:52,060
I'm just saying, it's not clear
if they're a thing or it's official.

1014
01:04:52,130 --> 01:04:55,460
- You'll probably find out tomorrow.
- Tomorrow?

1015
01:04:55,460 --> 01:04:57,670
I was thinking of planning
a little surprise for them.

1016
01:04:58,070 --> 01:05:01,600
- I turned off my location tracking.
- I guess I've been abandoned again.

1017
01:05:01,740 --> 01:05:03,940
Call the police
and have them find her! Now!
